      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The result of a <ph id=\"ph1\">`DeleteAsync`</ph> call is usually <ph id=\"ph2\">`null`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        15346,
        15399
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The ID to pass in can be obtained from the result of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`InsertAsync`</ph> call.",
      "pos": [
        15400,
        15476
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you try to delete an item without the \"Id\" field already set, a <ph id=\"ph1\">`MobileServiceInvalidOperationException`</ph> is returned from the backend.",
      "pos": [
        15477,
        15616
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        15621,
        15672
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"#custom-api\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Call a custom API"
    },
    {
      "content": "A custom API enables you to define custom endpoints that expose server functionality that does not map to an insert, update, delete, or read operation.",
      "pos": [
        15674,
        15825
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By using a custom API, you can have more control over messaging, including reading and setting HTTP message headers and defining a message body format other than JSON.",
      "pos": [
        15826,
        15993
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You call a custom API by calling one of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">InvokeApiAsync]</ept> method overloads on the client.",
      "pos": [
        15996,
        16088
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, the following line of code sends a POST request to the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>completeAll<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> API on the backend:",
      "pos": [
        16089,
        16192
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that this a typed method call, which requires that the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>MarkAllResult<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> return type be defined.",
      "pos": [
        16338,
        16439
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Both typed and untyped methods are supported.",
      "pos": [
        16440,
        16485
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This is an almost trivial example as it is typed, sends no payload, has no query parameters, and doesn't change the request headers.",
      "pos": [
        16486,
        16618
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more realistic examples and a more a complete discussion of <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">InvokeApiAsync]</ept>, see <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p2\">Custom API in Azure Mobile Services Client SDKs]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        16619,
        16755
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How to: Register for push notifications",
      "pos": [
        16759,
        16798
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Mobile Apps client enables you to register for push notifications with Azure Notification Hubs.",
      "pos": [
        16800,
        16899
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When registering, you obtain a handle that you obtain from the platform-specific Push Notification Service (PNS).",
      "pos": [
        16900,
        17013
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You then provide this value along with any tags when you create the registration.",
      "pos": [
        17014,
        17095
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following code registers your Windows app for push notifications with the Windows Notification Service (WNS):",
      "pos": [
        17096,
        17209
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that in this example, two tags are included with the registration.",
      "pos": [
        17719,
        17790
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information on Windows apps, including how to register for template registrations, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Add push notifications to your app<ept id=\"p1\">](app-service-mobile-windows-store-dotnet-get-started-push.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        17791,
        17985
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Xamarin apps require some additional code to be able to register an app running on iOS or Android app with the Apple Push Notification Service (APNS) and Google Cloud Messaging (GCM) services, respectively.",
      "pos": [
        17988,
        18194
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information see <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add push notifications to your app<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> (<bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Xamarin.iOS<ept id=\"p2\">](partner-xamarin-mobile-services-ios-get-started-push.md#add-push)</ept> | <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>Xamarin.Android<ept id=\"p3\">](partner-xamarin-mobile-services-android-get-started-push.md#add-push)</ept>).",
      "pos": [
        18195,
        18431
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How to: Register push templates to send cross-platform notifications",
      "pos": [
        18436,
        18504
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        18506,
        18637
      ],
      "content": "To register templates, simply pass along templates with your <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>MobileService.GetPush().RegisterAsync()<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> method in your client app."
    },
    {
      "content": "Your templates will be of type JObject and can contain multiple templates in the following JSON format:",
      "pos": [
        18716,
        18819
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        19572,
        19632
      ],
      "content": "The method <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>RegisterAsync()<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> also accepts Secondary Tiles:"
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that all tags will be stripped away for security.",
      "pos": [
        19744,
        19798
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To add tags to installations or templates within installations, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">Work with the .NET backend server SDK for Azure Mobile Apps]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        19799,
        19929
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        19931,
        20082
      ],
      "content": "To send notifications utilizing these registered templates, work with <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Notification Hubs APIs<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn495101.aspx)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        20086,
        20156
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"optimisticconcurrency\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Use Optimistic Concurrency"
    },
    {
      "content": "Two or more clients may write changes to the same item, at the same time, in some scenarios.",
      "pos": [
        20158,
        20250
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Without any conflict detection, the last write would overwrite any previous updates even if this was not the desired result.",
      "pos": [
        20251,
        20375
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Optimistic concurrency control<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> assumes that each transaction can commit and therefore does not use any resource locking.",
      "pos": [
        20376,
        20498
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Before committing a transaction, optimistic concurrency control verifies that no other transaction has modified the data.",
      "pos": [
        20499,
        20620
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the data has been modified, the committing transaction is rolled back.",
      "pos": [
        20621,
        20694
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Mobile Apps supports optimistic concurrency control by tracking changes to each item using the <ph id=\"ph1\">`__version`</ph> system property column that is defined for each table in your Mobile App backend.",
      "pos": [
        20696,
        20884
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each time a record is updated, Mobile Apps sets the <ph id=\"ph1\">`__version`</ph> property for that record to a new value.",
      "pos": [
        20885,
        20989
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "During each update request, the <ph id=\"ph1\">`__version`</ph> property of the record included with the request is compared to the same property for the record on the server.",
      "pos": [
        20990,
        21145
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If the version passed with the request does not match the backend, then the client library raises a <ph id=\"ph1\">`MobileServicePreconditionFailedException&lt;T&gt;`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        21146,
        21292
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The type included with the exception is the record from the backend containing the server's version of the record.",
      "pos": [
        21293,
        21407
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The application can then use this information to decide whether to execute the update request again with the correct <ph id=\"ph1\">`__version`</ph> value from the backend to commit changes.",
      "pos": [
        21408,
        21578
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To enable optimistic concurrency the application defines a column on the table class for the <ph id=\"ph1\">`__version`</ph> system property.",
      "pos": [
        21582,
        21703
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following definition provides an example.",
      "pos": [
        21704,
        21749
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        22160,
        22304
      ],
      "content": "Applications using untyped tables enable optimistic concurrency by setting the <ph id=\"ph1\">`Version`</ph> flag on the <ph id=\"ph2\">`SystemProperties`</ph> of the table as follows."
    },
    {
      "content": "The following code shows how to resolve a write conflict once detected.",
      "pos": [
        22441,
        22512
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The correct <ph id=\"ph1\">`__version`</ph> value must be included in the <ph id=\"ph2\">`UpdateAsync()`</ph> call to commit a resolution.",
      "pos": [
        22513,
        22611
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        24589,
        24701
      ],
      "content": "For more information, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Offline Data Sync in Azure Mobile Apps<ept id=\"p1\">](app-service-mobile-offline-data-sync.md)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        24706,
        24785
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"binding\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Bind Mobile Apps data to a Windows user interface"
    },
    {
      "content": "This section shows how to display returned data objects using UI elements in a Windows app.",
      "pos": [
        24787,
        24878
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To query incomplete items in <ph id=\"ph1\">`todoTable`</ph> and display it in a very simple list, you can run the following example code to bind the source of the list with a query.",
      "pos": [
        24879,
        25041
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Using <ph id=\"ph1\">`MobileServiceCollection`</ph> creates a Mobile Apps-aware binding collection.",
      "pos": [
        25042,
        25121
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Some controls in the managed runtime support an interface called <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ISupportIncrementalLoading<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/Hh701916)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        25542,
        25693
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This interface allows controls to request extra data when the user scrolls.",
      "pos": [
        25694,
        25769
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There is built-in support for this interface for universal Windows 8.1 apps via <ph id=\"ph1\">`MobileServiceIncrementalLoadingCollection`</ph>, which automatically handles the calls from the controls.",
      "pos": [
        25770,
        25951
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To use <ph id=\"ph1\">`MobileServiceIncrementalLoadingCollection`</ph> in Windows apps, do the following:",
      "pos": [
        25952,
        26037
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To use the new collection on Windows Phone 8 and \"Silverlight\" apps, use the <ph id=\"ph1\">`ToCollection`</ph> extension methods on <ph id=\"ph2\">`IMobileServiceTableQuery&lt;T&gt;`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">`IMobileServiceTable&lt;T&gt;`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        26318,
        26490
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To actually load data, call <ph id=\"ph1\">`LoadMoreItemsAsync()`</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        26491,
        26542
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you use the collection created by calling <ph id=\"ph1\">`ToCollectionAsync`</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">`ToCollection`</ph>, you get a collection which can be bound to UI controls.",
      "pos": [
        26709,
        26850
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This collection is paging-aware, i.e., a control can ask the collection to \"load more items\", and the collection will do it for the control.",
      "pos": [
        26851,
        26991
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At that point there is no user code involved, the control will start the flow.",
      "pos": [
        26992,
        27070
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, since the collection is loading data from the network, it's expected that some times this loading will fail.",
      "pos": [
        27071,
        27188
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To handle such failures, you may override the <ph id=\"ph1\">`OnException`</ph> method on <ph id=\"ph2\">`MobileServiceIncrementalLoadingCollection`</ph> to handle exceptions resulting from calls to <ph id=\"ph3\">`LoadMoreItemsAsync`</ph> performed by controls.",
      "pos": [
        27189,
        27391
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Finally, imagine that your table has many fields, but you only want to display some of them in your control.",
      "pos": [
        27393,
        27501
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You may use the guidance in the section \"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Select specific columns<ept id=\"p1\">](#selecting)</ept>\" above to select specific columns to display in the UI.",
      "pos": [
        27502,
        27636
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        27641,
        27709
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"package-sid\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Obtain a Windows Store package SID"
    },
    {
      "content": "For Windows apps, a package SID is needed for enabling push notifications and certain authentication modes.",
      "pos": [
        27711,
        27818
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To obtain this value:",
      "pos": [
        27819,
        27840
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        27845,
        27978
      ],
      "content": "In Visual Studio Solution Explorer, right-click the Windows Store app project, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Store<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> &gt; <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Associate App with the Store...<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        27982,
        28129
      ],
      "content": "In the wizard, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Next<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, sign in with your Microsoft account, type a name for your app in <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Reserve a new app name<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, then click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Reserve<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "After the app registration is successfully created, select the new app name, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Next<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Associate<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        28133,
        28255
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This adds the required Windows Store registration information to the application manifest.",
      "pos": [
        28256,
        28346
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Log into the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Dev Center<ept id=\"p1\">](https://dev.windows.com/en-us/overview)</ept> using your Microsoft Account.",
      "pos": [
        28350,
        28453
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Under <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>My apps<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, click the app registration you just created.",
      "pos": [
        28454,
        28517
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        28521,
        28616
      ],
      "content": "Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>App management<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> &gt; <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>App identity<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, and then scroll down to find your <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Package SID<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Many uses of the package SID treat it as a URI, in which case you will need to use <bpt id=\"p1\">_</bpt>ms-app://<ept id=\"p1\">_</ept> as the scheme.",
      "pos": [
        28618,
        28727
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make note of the version of your package SID formed by concatenating this value as a prefix.",
      "pos": [
        28728,
        28820
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        37716,
        37758
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"errors\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Handle errors"
    },
    {
      "content": "The following example shows you how to handle an exception that is returned by the backend:",
      "pos": [
        37760,
        37851
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        38326,
        38378
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"unit-testing\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Design unit tests"
    },
    {
      "content": "The value returned by <ph id=\"ph1\">`MobileServiceClient.GetTable`</ph> and the queries are interfaces.",
      "pos": [
        38380,
        38464
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "That makes them easily \"mockable\" for testing purposes, so you could create a <ph id=\"ph1\">`MyMockTable : IMobileServiceTable&lt;TodoItem&gt;`</ph> that implements your testing logic.",
      "pos": [
        38465,
        38624
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        38628,
        38682
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"customizing\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Customize the client"
    },
    {
      "content": "This section shows ways in which you can customize the request headers and customize the serialization of JSON objects in the response.",
      "pos": [
        38684,
        38819
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        38825,
        38880
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"headers\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Customize request headers"
    },
    {
      "content": "To support your specific app scenario, you might need to customize communication with the Mobile App backend.",
      "pos": [
        38882,
        38991
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, you may want to add a custom header to every outgoing request or even change responses status codes.",
      "pos": [
        38992,
        39105
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can do this by providing a custom <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">DelegatingHandler]</ept>, as in the following example:",
      "pos": [
        39106,
        39193
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This code adds a new <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>x-my-header<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> header in the request and arbitrarily sets the response code to unavailable.",
      "pos": [
        40158,
        40271
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In a real-world scenario, you would set the response status code based on some custom logic required by your app.",
      "pos": [
        40272,
        40385
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        40391,
        40450
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"serialization\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Customize serialization"
    },
    {
      "content": "The Mobile Apps client library uses Json.NET to convert a JSON response into .NET objects on the client.",
      "pos": [
        40452,
        40556
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can configure the behavior of this serialization between .NET types and JSON in the messages.",
      "pos": [
        40557,
        40654
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">MobileServiceClient]</ept> class exposes a <ph id=\"ph1\">`SerializerSettings`</ph> property of type <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>JsonSerializerSettings<ept id=\"p2\">](http://james.newtonking.com/projects/json/help/?topic=html/T_Newtonsoft_Json_JsonSerializerSettings.htm)</ept>",
      "pos": [
        40655,
        40864
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Using this property, you may set one of the many Json.NET properties, such as the following:",
      "pos": [
        40866,
        40958
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This property converts all properties to lower case during serialization.",
      "pos": [
        41130,
        41203
      ]
    }
